modules.description: Handles asynchronous connection attempts to remote hosts with multiple address families, prioritizing IPv6 while falling back to IPv4. Operates on socket addresses, connection states, and timeout configurations. Used to establish reliable network connections in environments with mixed IPv4/IPv6 support.

Provides functions to establish connections using the Happy Eyeballs algorithm, supporting IP address resolution and DNS injection. Operates with IP addresses, domain names, and custom DNS resolvers through the `getaddrinfo` type. Enables connection attempts to hosts or IP addresses with configurable timeouts and retries, and allows injecting DNS resolution after initial setup.
